# E2E tests must not change app behavior for testability

When fixing or writing Playwright tests, **do not modify application source code** (`src/**`) to make tests pass.

## When tests fail

Follow this order:

1. **Fix the tests** — update locators, waits, and assertions to match current app behavior
2. **Note real bugs separately** — if a failure exposes a production issue, call it out explicitly; do not fold the fix into "debugging tests" silently
3. **Ask before touching `src/`** — get approval before any production change, even when the test revealed a legitimate bug

Do not bend UI state, defaults, or business logic so stale assertions pass. The test should observe the app; the app should not be reshaped for the test.

### Legitimate `src/` fixes (with approval)

Some failures expose real bugs unrelated to testability. These are OK to fix in `src/**` after calling them out — typically in the data layer, not UI:

- Query cache not updated on mutation (e.g. list cache patched but detail cache stale)
- Server function returning wrong shape
- Actual broken user-facing behavior the test correctly caught

Still **not** OK: changing component defaults, layout, or feature behavior to match what the test used to expect.

## Allowed in `src/**` for E2E

- Adding or updating `data-testid` attributes on existing elements

## Not allowed in `src/**` for E2E

- Hydration markers (`data-hydrated`, `data-ready`, mount `useEffect` flags)
- Test-only props, exports, or conditional branches
- Renaming or duplicating testids on loading/skeleton UI to satisfy timing
- Reverting or changing app defaults/state so tests pass (e.g. toggling `showActivity`, re-adding effects)
- Any other production change whose sole purpose is test synchronization

## Fix flakiness in tests instead

- Wait for loaded UI (`AddListContainer`, not a shared pending-shell testid)
- For SSR hydration races, poll in the page with `page.waitForFunction` until interaction works
- Use Playwright retries: `expect(async () => { ... }).toPass()`
- Seed data via `/__test/*` helpers and assert on rendered UI
- Prefer roles and existing `data-testid`s over new production hooks

## Do not assert on CSS in tests

Assert on rendered UI via `data-testid`, roles, text, or attributes — not computed styles (`toHaveCSS`, color tokens, layout values). If a visual state needs verifying, add a `data-testid` on the element that represents that state.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — assert via test id
await expect(
  completionCircle.getByTestId('CardCompletedIndicatorCheckmark'),
).toBeVisible();

// ❌ BAD — couples tests to styling implementation
await expect(completionCircle).toHaveCSS('background-color', 'rgb(31, 132, 90)');
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — test-only hydration wait (no src/ changes)
await expect(page.getByTestId('AddListContainer')).toBeVisible();
await page.waitForFunction(() => {
  if (document.querySelector('[data-testid="AddListInput"]')) return true;
  document
    .querySelector('[data-testid="AddListContainer"] button')
    ?.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true }));
  return !!document.querySelector('[data-testid="AddListInput"]');
});

// ❌ BAD — app hook only for tests
// <AddListContainer data-hydrated={hydrated ? '' : undefined} />
```
